{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":959,"text":"There are things we say"},{"time":2261,"text":"when we catch the eye of a stranger"},{"time":4681,"text":"or a neighbor walking by."},{"time":7530,"text":"We say, \"Hello, how are you?"},{"time":10080,"text":"It's a beautiful day."},{"time":11812,"text":"How do you feel?\""},{"time":13552,"text":"These sound kind of meaningless, right?\nAnd, in some ways, they are."},{"time":17210,"text":"They have no semantic meaning."},{"time":20500,"text":"It doesn't matter how you are\nor what the day is like."},{"time":23934,"text":"They have something else."},{"time":25425,"text":"They have social meaning."},{"time":28051,"text":"What we mean when we say those things is:"},{"time":30554,"text":"I see you there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33764,"text":"I'm obsessed with talking to strangers."},{"time":37122,"text":"I make eye contact, say hello,"},{"time":39499,"text":"I offer help, I listen."},{"time":42699,"text":"I get all kinds of stories."},{"time":45773,"text":"About seven years ago, I started\ndocumenting my experiences"},{"time":49064,"text":"to try to figure out why."},{"time":51900,"text":"What I found was that something\nreally beautiful was going on."},{"time":55963,"text":"This is almost poetic."},{"time":58184,"text":"These were really profound experiences."},{"time":61478,"text":"They were unexpected pleasures."},{"time":63382,"text":"They were genuine emotional connections."},{"time":66370,"text":"They were liberating moments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70098,"text":"So one day, I was standing on a corner\nwaiting for the light to change,"},{"time":74226,"text":"which, I'm a New Yorker,"},{"time":75559,"text":"so that means I was actually standing\nin the street on the storm drain,"},{"time":79667,"text":"as if that could get me across faster."},{"time":82038,"text":"And there's an old man\nstanding next to me."},{"time":84063,"text":"So he's wearing, like, a long overcoat\nand sort of an old-man hat,"},{"time":88914,"text":"and he looked like somebody from a movie."},{"time":91064,"text":"And he says to me,"},{"time":92286,"text":"\"Don't stand there. You might disappear.\""},{"time":96095,"text":"So this is absurd, right?"},{"time":97386,"text":"But I did what he said.\nI stepped back onto the sidewalk."},{"time":100697,"text":"And he smiled, and he said,"},{"time":102613,"text":"\"Good. You never know."},{"time":104518,"text":"I might have turned around,"},{"time":105969,"text":"and zoop, you're gone.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":109553,"text":"This was weird,"},{"time":111638,"text":"and also really wonderful."},{"time":114091,"text":"He was so warm, and he was\nso happy that he'd saved me."},{"time":117977,"text":"We had this little bond."},{"time":119987,"text":"For a minute, I felt like\nmy existence as a person"},{"time":124174,"text":"had been noticed,"},{"time":126335,"text":"and I was worth saving."},{"time":131058,"text":"The really sad thing is,"},{"time":132709,"text":"in many parts of the world,"},{"time":134406,"text":"we're raised to believe\nthat strangers are dangerous by default,"},{"time":138360,"text":"that we can't trust them,\nthat they might hurt us."},{"time":142389,"text":"But most strangers aren't dangerous."},{"time":144991,"text":"We're uneasy around them\nbecause we have no context."},{"time":148807,"text":"We don't know what their intentions are."},{"time":151028,"text":"So instead of using our perceptions\nand making choices,"},{"time":154835,"text":"we rely on this category of \"stranger.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":159012,"text":"I have a four-year-old."},{"time":160862,"text":"When I say hello to people on the street,"},{"time":162861,"text":"she asks me why."},{"time":164820,"text":"She says, \"Do we know them?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":168324,"text":"I say, \"No, they're our neighbor.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":170895,"text":"\"Are they our friend?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":172941,"text":"\"No, it's just good to be friendly.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":175773,"text":"I think twice every time\nI say that to her,"},{"time":179126,"text":"because I mean it,\nbut as a woman, particularly,"},{"time":182658,"text":"I know that not every stranger\non the street has the best intentions."},{"time":186873,"text":"It is good to be friendly,\nand it's good to learn when not to be,"},{"time":190751,"text":"but none of that means\nwe have to be afraid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194451,"text":"There are two huge benefits"},{"time":197348,"text":"to using our senses instead of our fears."},{"time":201015,"text":"The first one is that it liberates us."},{"time":205970,"text":"When you think about it,"},{"time":207867,"text":"using perception instead of categories"},{"time":210103,"text":"is much easier said than done."},{"time":212859,"text":"Categories are something our brains use."},{"time":215693,"text":"When it comes to people,"},{"time":217354,"text":"it's sort of a shortcut\nfor learning about them."},{"time":220900,"text":"We see male, female, young, old,"},{"time":224562,"text":"black, brown, white, stranger, friend,"},{"time":228948,"text":"and we use the information in that box."},{"time":232112,"text":"It's quick, it's easy"},{"time":233854,"text":"and it's a road to bias."},{"time":236052,"text":"And it means we're not thinking\nabout people as individuals."},{"time":241774,"text":"I know an American researcher\nwho travels frequently"},{"time":245135,"text":"in Central Asia and Africa, alone."},{"time":248910,"text":"She's entering into towns and cities"},{"time":251473,"text":"as a complete stranger."},{"time":253937,"text":"She has no bonds, no connections."},{"time":256126,"text":"She's a foreigner."},{"time":257957,"text":"Her survival strategy is this:"},{"time":260357,"text":"get one stranger to see you\nas a real, individual person."},{"time":264839,"text":"If you can do that, it'll help\nother people see you that way, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268817,"text":"The second benefit of using our senses\nhas to do with intimacy."},{"time":274003,"text":"I know it sounds\na little counterintuitive,"},{"time":276422,"text":"intimacy and strangers,"},{"time":278543,"text":"but these quick interactions\ncan lead to a feeling"},{"time":282619,"text":"that sociologists call\n\"fleeting intimacy.\""},{"time":285785,"text":"So, it's a brief experience\nthat has emotional resonance and meaning."},{"time":291452,"text":"It's the good feeling I got"},{"time":293484,"text":"from being saved from the death trap\nof the storm drain by the old man,"},{"time":298610,"text":"or how I feel like part of a community"},{"time":301134,"text":"when I talk to somebody\non my train on the way to work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305665,"text":"Sometimes it goes further."},{"time":307713,"text":"Researchers have found\nthat people often feel more comfortable"},{"time":312850,"text":"being honest and open\nabout their inner selves with strangers"},{"time":316118,"text":"than they do with their friends\nand their families --"},{"time":320110,"text":"that they often feel\nmore understood by strangers."},{"time":325022,"text":"This gets reported in the media\nwith great lament."},{"time":329125,"text":"\"Strangers communicate\nbetter than spouses!\""},{"time":332901,"text":"It's a good headline, right?"},{"time":335547,"text":"I think it entirely misses the point."},{"time":339240,"text":"The important thing about these studies"},{"time":341177,"text":"is just how significant\nthese interactions can be;"},{"time":344795,"text":"how this special form of closeness"},{"time":347923,"text":"gives us something we need\nas much as we need our friends"},{"time":350725,"text":"and our families."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352933,"text":"So how is it possible that we communicate\nso well with strangers?"},{"time":358585,"text":"There are two reasons."},{"time":360245,"text":"The first one is that\nit's a quick interaction."},{"time":363183,"text":"It has no consequences."},{"time":365034,"text":"It's easy to be honest with someone\nyou're never going to see again, right?"},{"time":368643,"text":"That makes sense."},{"time":370177,"text":"The second reason is where\nit gets more interesting."},{"time":373085,"text":"We have a bias when it comes\nto people we're close to."},{"time":377359,"text":"We expect them to understand us."},{"time":380550,"text":"We assume they do,"},{"time":381803,"text":"and we expect them to read our minds."},{"time":384717,"text":"So imagine you're at a party,"},{"time":387045,"text":"and you can't believe\nthat your friend or your spouse"},{"time":390671,"text":"isn't picking up on it\nthat you want to leave early."},{"time":393498,"text":"And you're thinking,"},{"time":394896,"text":"\"I gave you the look.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":398696,"text":"With a stranger, we have\nto start from scratch."},{"time":401235,"text":"We tell the whole story,"},{"time":403376,"text":"we explain who the people are,\nhow we feel about them;"},{"time":406488,"text":"we spell out all the inside jokes."},{"time":408680,"text":"And guess what?"},{"time":410180,"text":"Sometimes they do\nunderstand us a little better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414087,"text":"OK."},{"time":415271,"text":"So now that we know\nthat talking to strangers matters,"},{"time":418791,"text":"how does it work?"},{"time":420721,"text":"There are unwritten rules\nwe tend to follow."},{"time":423495,"text":"The rules are very different\ndepending on what country you're in,"},{"time":427315,"text":"what culture you're in."},{"time":429032,"text":"In most parts of the US,"},{"time":431185,"text":"the baseline expectation in public"},{"time":433464,"text":"is that we maintain a balance\nbetween civility and privacy."},{"time":438180,"text":"This is known as civil inattention."},{"time":441263,"text":"So, imagine two people are walking\ntowards each other on the street."},{"time":445047,"text":"They'll glance at each other\nfrom a distance."},{"time":447369,"text":"That's the civility, the acknowledgment."},{"time":449375,"text":"And then as they get closer,\nthey'll look away,"},{"time":451606,"text":"to give each other some space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455151,"text":"In other cultures,"},{"time":456437,"text":"people go to extraordinary lengths\nnot to interact at all."},{"time":462533,"text":"People from Denmark tell me"},{"time":464791,"text":"that many Danes are so averse\nto talking to strangers,"},{"time":468423,"text":"that they would rather\nmiss their stop on the bus"},{"time":471665,"text":"than say \"excuse me\" to someone\nthat they need to get around."},{"time":475040,"text":"Instead, there's this elaborate\nshuffling of bags"},{"time":478353,"text":"and using your body to say\nthat you need to get past,"},{"time":481860,"text":"instead of using two words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486178,"text":"In Egypt, I'm told,"},{"time":488731,"text":"it's rude to ignore a stranger,"},{"time":491047,"text":"and there's a remarkable\nculture of hospitality."},{"time":495312,"text":"Strangers might ask each other\nfor a sip of water."},{"time":498392,"text":"Or, if you ask someone for directions,"},{"time":501120,"text":"they're very likely\nto invite you home for coffee."},{"time":505441,"text":"We see these unwritten rules\nmost clearly when they're broken,"},{"time":509563,"text":"or when you're in a new place"},{"time":511670,"text":"and you're trying to figure out\nwhat the right thing to do is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515332,"text":"Sometimes breaking the rules a little bit\nis where the action is."},{"time":522551,"text":"In case it's not clear,\nI really want you to do this. OK?"},{"time":527790,"text":"So here's how it's going to go."},{"time":529703,"text":"Find somebody who is making eye contact."},{"time":531753,"text":"That's a good signal."},{"time":533466,"text":"The first thing is a simple smile."},{"time":536402,"text":"If you're passing somebody on the street\nor in the hallway here, smile."},{"time":540342,"text":"See what happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542113,"text":"Another is triangulation."},{"time":544552,"text":"There's you, there's a stranger,"},{"time":546255,"text":"there's some third thing\nthat you both might see and comment on,"},{"time":551134,"text":"like a piece of public art"},{"time":553145,"text":"or somebody preaching in the street"},{"time":555659,"text":"or somebody wearing funny clothes."},{"time":558689,"text":"Give it a try."},{"time":559864,"text":"Make a comment about that third thing,\nand see if starts a conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564621,"text":"Another is what I call noticing."},{"time":566369,"text":"This is usually giving a compliment."},{"time":569003,"text":"I'm a big fan of noticing people's shoes."},{"time":572283,"text":"I'm actually not wearing\nfabulous shoes right now,"},{"time":575063,"text":"but shoes are fabulous in general."},{"time":577817,"text":"And they're pretty neutral\nas far as giving compliments goes."},{"time":581967,"text":"People always want to tell you things\nabout their awesome shoes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585599,"text":"You may have already experienced\nthe dogs and babies principle."},{"time":589520,"text":"It can be awkward\nto talk to someone on the street;"},{"time":591962,"text":"you don't know how\nthey're going to respond."},{"time":594057,"text":"But you can always talk\nto their dog or their baby."},{"time":596623,"text":"The dog or the baby"},{"time":597996,"text":"is a social conduit to the person,"},{"time":601095,"text":"and you can tell by how they respond"},{"time":603156,"text":"whether they're open to talking more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606156,"text":"The last one I want to challenge you to"},{"time":608345,"text":"is disclosure."},{"time":610548,"text":"This is a very vulnerable thing to do,"},{"time":612914,"text":"and it can be very rewarding."},{"time":615068,"text":"So next time you're talking to a stranger"},{"time":617726,"text":"and you feel comfortable,"},{"time":619966,"text":"tell them something true about yourself,"},{"time":622340,"text":"something really personal."},{"time":624103,"text":"You might have that experience\nI talked about of feeling understood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629854,"text":"Sometimes in conversation, it comes up,"},{"time":631824,"text":"people ask me, \"What does your dad do?\"\nor, \"Where does he live?\""},{"time":635205,"text":"And sometimes I tell them the whole truth,"},{"time":637451,"text":"which is that he died when I was a kid."},{"time":641386,"text":"Always in those moments,"},{"time":643427,"text":"they share their own experiences of loss."},{"time":646407,"text":"We tend to meet\ndisclosure with disclosure,"},{"time":649567,"text":"even with strangers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652453,"text":"So, here it is."},{"time":655425,"text":"When you talk to strangers,\nyou're making beautiful interruptions"},{"time":659303,"text":"into the expected narrative\nof your daily life"},{"time":662813,"text":"and theirs."},{"time":664790,"text":"You're making unexpected connections."},{"time":667420,"text":"If you don't talk to strangers,\nyou're missing out on all of that."},{"time":673544,"text":"We spend a lot of time"},{"time":675846,"text":"teaching our children about strangers."},{"time":678764,"text":"What would happen if we spent\nmore time teaching ourselves?"},{"time":683441,"text":"We could reject all the ideas\nthat make us so suspicious of each other."},{"time":688649,"text":"We could make a space for change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692141,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693316,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}